data.title: Texas Counties
data.meta_description: There are 254 counties in Texas. How many can you name?
data.text:
I've lived in Texas my whole life (well, 9 years in California), I've lived in several cities, I've traveled, I've done genealogy research on my Texas ancestors who go back to pre-1836. And still I got only 60 correct, and that included a lot of wild guessing. (Let's enter some common last names! What about rivers? What about colors? Plants?)

I'm most unhappy about missing Harris County. I was going through the alphabet trying to remember it, and when I got to H my brain perked upâ€”but I calmed it down again by telling it it was only excited because of the H in Houston.

I'm not sure I'm up for mastering this one!
